From: Florian Eckert <fe@dev.tdt.de>
Date: Fri, 19 Dec 2025 08:04:28 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] phy: intel: phy-intel-lgm-combo: Log combophy mode

The intel combo PHY can be configured in different modes via the
devicetree. Therefore, it makes sense to output this during bootup.

Signed-off-by: Florian Eckert <fe@dev.tdt.de>
---
 drivers/phy/intel/phy-intel-lgm-combo.c | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/phy/intel/phy-intel-lgm-combo.c b/drivers/phy/intel/phy-intel-lgm-combo.c
index f8e3054a9e59..6b0f57b11639 100644
--- a/drivers/phy/intel/phy-intel-lgm-combo.c
+++ b/drivers/phy/intel/phy-intel-lgm-combo.c
@@ -69,6 +69,15 @@ enum intel_combo_mode {
 	SATA0_SATA1_MODE,
 };
 
+static const char * const cbphy_mode_names[] = {
+	"PCIe single lane mode",
+	"PCIe Dual lane mode",
+	"RXAUI mode",
+	"XFI single lane mode",
+	"SATA single lane mode",
+	"PHY mode not supported"
+};
+
 enum aggregated_mode {
 	PHY_SL_MODE,
 	PHY_DL_MODE,
@@ -232,6 +241,9 @@ static int intel_cbphy_set_mode(struct intel_combo_phy *cbphy)
 	if (ret)
 		dev_err(dev, "Failed to set ComboPhy mode: %d\n", ret);
 
+	dev_info(dev, "Set combo mode: combophy[%d]: mode: %s\n",
+		cbphy->id, cbphy_mode_names[cb_mode]);
+
 	return ret;
 }
 
